corandil?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Acts as both a potassium channel activator and nitric oxide donor","Inhibits beta-adrenergic receptors in cardiac tissue","Reduces cholesterol synthesis in hepatocytes","Prevents platelet aggregation and thrombosis","Blocks calcium channels in vascular smooth muscle"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003ENicorandil has a unique dual mechanism of action. It \u003Cstrong\u003Eacts as both a potassium channel activator and nitric oxide donor\u003C/strong\u003E. The potassium channel activation hyperpolarises vascular smooth muscle cells, while the nitric oxide component stimulates guanylate cyclase. Both mechanisms lead to vasodilation.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EBlocks calcium channels in vascular smooth muscle\u003C/strong\u003E describes the mechanism of calcium channel blockers such as amlodipine.\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EInhibits beta-adrenergic receptors in cardiac tissue\u003C/strong\u003E describes the mechanism of beta blockers such as metoprolol.\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPrevents platelet aggregation and thrombosis\u003C/strong\u003E describes the mechanism of antiplatelet medications such as aspirin.\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EReduces cholesterol synthesis in hepatocytes\u003C/strong\u003E describes the mechanism of statins such as atorvastatin.\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe combined vasodilatory effects of nicorandil reduce both preload and afterload on the heart, improving the balance between myocardial oxygen supply and demand in patients with angina. The peripheral vasodilation reduces afterload, while venodilation reduces preload. Additionally, coronary vasodilation directly improves myocardial oxygen supply.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["Nicorandil is a vasodilator that acts through both potassium channel activation and nitric oxide donation.","Nicorandil is used to treat stable angina by reducing cardiac preload and afterload.","The dual mechanism of action of nicorandil provides more effective coronary vasodilation than either mechanism alone.","Nicorandil reduces myocardial oxygen demand while simultaneously improving coronary blood flow."],"references":["Therapeutic Guidelines. Melbourne: Therapeutic Guidelines Limited. Available from: https://www.tg.org.au","Ritter J, Flower RJ (Rod J), Henderson G (Graeme), et al.\u00a0Rang and Dale\u2019s Pharmacology. Tenth edition. Elsevier; 2024.","Australian Medicines Handbook\u00a0(online). Adelaide: Australian Medicines Handbook Pty Ltd. Available from:\u00a0https://amhonline.amh.net.au/"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"54095"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17125"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"54095","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/54095"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-10T08:57:42+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-10T08:58:41+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"9815"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"68638"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},